              incorrectFeedback: 'At 1.8 cal/cm², PPE is required (above the 1.2 cal/cm² threshold), but Category 1 (4 cal/cm² minimum) is sufficient. Higher categories are needed when incident energy exceeds 4 cal/cm² (Cat 2) or 8 cal/cm² (Cat 3). Over-PPE causes heat stress — select the right category, not the highest available.',
